member.example:
This sample shows how to call GetWritableUriAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var client = new DataStreamLogsContainerClient(credential);

Response response = await client.GetWritableUriAsync("<measurementId>", "<dataStreamId>");

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("logFolderUri").ToString());

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the response payload.

Response Body:

Schema for DataStreamLogsContainerBase:
{
  logFolderUri: string, # Required.
}

